data.name: Honey Mustard Glazed Pork Chops
data.quickTastyDescription: Juicy pork chops glazed with a sweet and tangy honey mustard sauce, perfect for a simple yet delicious meal.
detailedCookingInstructions: In a small bowl, whisk together honey and Dijon mustard until well combined.
Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat.
Season pork chops with garlic powder, salt, and pepper on both sides.
Add pork chops to the skillet and cook for about 4-5 minutes on each side until browned.
During the last minute of cooking, pour the honey mustard mixture over the pork chops, allowing it to glaze the meat.
Remove from heat and let rest for a few minutes before serving.
